caption: I tried for the first time with a group (5 of us total) and would not return. My drink order was correct after the third try and still wasn’t good or worth the price. One of the times I was given a drink that I didn’t order, only to be told after it arrived that they ran out of tequila. Understandable! But that should be communicated before I order (or at least ask if I want something else instead of just giving me an alternate). Service was borderline rude and confusing throughout. No manager ever touched our table.  The food was actually good and a highlight but two of those in my group had the wrong order/specifications.  I am a lifelong service industry person, so all of this could be written off as a bad night. But after reading responses to other reviews by the owner, I am amazed that they (or whomever is running the account) would respond to guests in such an accusatory, pretentious, short, and rude manner.

Served me raw burgers. Ordered from doordash and the restaurant lost my order. The driver had to wait 25 minutes, call doordash HQ, and then it comes out looking like this. Theyre clearly inedible, and unsafe to serve to customers.

I cannot express how good these burgers are. Truly the best. I eat here at alarming frequency and have never once regretted it. Literally everything on the menu is incredible. They’ve nailed fried chicken. Perfected grilled chicken. Every actual burger is outrageous. I’m often brought to tears by how good these burgers actually are. Literally may have this establishment cater my wedding.
Best burger in DC. And I’ve been to the diplomat, Duke’s, and the other top contenders.

I’ve had lucky buns several times. Honestly one of the best burgers I’ve had in DC. Cooked perfectly every time and all of there burgers are packed with flavor.  @Turki you probably still ate the whole burger.
So I almost want to say it was good , my friend and I ordered 3 burgers and the last one was too salty and they still charged us for it .

Truly good burger and homemade fried: the bun is good and not too greasy, I chose the spicy chicken and the meat was flavourful, crunchy and spicy enough to feel on your tongue, I totally recommend this address!! The service is nice as well and the price is fine, around $20 for fries and burger

I got takeout here a month ago and it wasn't the best burger, but I got takeout again last night and it was honestly soo good. The fried chicken I think as the change (a lot better than the beef I had a month ago IMO). Unfortunately, we got fries instead of the brussel sprouts that we ordered and they were not the best. BUT, will be back for that fried chicken burger!!
Great food and atmosphere. The mumbo bun is great.
Best burger in DC imo

I came to visit my SO for valentines and were walking about when it started to sleet/rain. We ran into this place.  Had a a few drinks (Pauly walnuts and mezcal Paloma) and couldn’t stop noticing how much take-out they were doing.  We weren’t too hungry, but curious. I asked: What is most popular?: Their name sake, Lucky Bun.  What is the hottest? Hot  Tiger Bun; Hot tiger bun, please (We likes it hot)!  Apparently, this thing has Szechuan pepper sauce. It is so CRONCH...much flavor...hot and spicy perfection!!!  If I lived here, I’d live off that alone weekly. Reminded me of Korean chili ramen... Yummmy hotttness!  Thanks to staff for humoring our escape from cold, wet weather with dank drinks and good advice.  Thank you!!

Food looks good and probably is but I couldn’t eat my food. I lost my appetite after seeing one of the workers dig in their buttocks several times and put on gloves without washing their hands. Another employee was grabbing their shoes, touching hair, body parts, etc and then put on gloves without washing his hands. Even after that they continued to grab outside belongings with the gloves and prepared my food. I brought this to their attention but was met with an attitude. I just couldn’t bring myself to eat it after seeing all of that.
Get the mumbo bun, you won't be disappointed.
Went to their stand in Union Market and got the best chicken sandwich I’ve ever had! Try the Mumbo Bun!
Solid buns selection (served in burger style, not bao style) and very welcoming firepit tables for outdoor dining. Friendly and professional service.
Great burger!
Obsessed. Best burgers in NW DC. Get the fried chicken Bun Mi and the Thick Cut Chips. Cocktails to go are great too.
Excellent burgers and friendly staff! Had a lovely dinner here with my partner and we both enjoyed our burgers thoroughly. We'll definitely be back, best burgers in DC definitely!
Amazing burgers!! I had the Bun Mi with grilled chicken and it was absolutely delicious!! Strongly recommended. Besides the staff is really friendly.
Service is top class. Food was hot and fantastic. They even stayed open a bit late to make my order <3  5/5 one of the better spots at Union Market

Not only did I think this was the best burger place in D.C. I think it may be the best restaurant in the city. I don't feel I can adequately put into words how delicious Lucky Buns is. My wife and I got two different burgers and the cheesy fries and each bite seemingly tasted better than the last. The staff was super friendly and welcoming. They told us about where they get their beef from and how they handcut their fries each day. Lucky Buns is incredible. 10/10. Would highly recommend.
Expect spicy poos after the tiger bun! Still worth it
Really awesome burgers, one of the best in DC! Go!

Hands down the tiger burger was the best burger I’ve ever had. Yes it is spicy but don’t be deterred by the ‘extreme spice’ tag to this burger. It is bursting with flavours can’t wait to come back to have this amazing halal burger and the other burgers too! Customer service is great.
Amazing burgers and curry fries!
I was soo excited to try this since the burgers are halal but, I was extremely disappointed. The burgers did not taste good and looked NOTHING like the pictures. I threw mine away.
Fries were terrible, my lucky burger tasted bland. This place is over hyped.
Visited on Sat I believe. Looking forward to a return trip. Not close to my job, I wish it was.
Excellent blends of different spices. All condiments and sauces compliments each other. Meat is tender and well cooked, bun is delicious. It was a party in my mouth.

Truly the best burger place in town. I continued to hear the hype but never went. After walking by, we popped in! I cannot recommend this place more now! The outdoor seating area is a plant lovers dream. The selection of beer is limited but extremely great options. No need for a reservation.  I will definitely go back (soon.)
Best burgers in DC

Simple, clean, fresh ingredients that pack a punch of flavor!!! Burger cooked to perfection and fresh veg gave great balance! Fries crispy not greasy! First time in town and to Lucky Buns. Highly recommend!
Great selection of burgers and all are delicious. Service was really good. Recommended!

Im reviewing their Union Market location, not 18th st.  Their union market location is not on google. The burger was overcooked and grey despite being ordered med rare.  But the burger also lacks any char on the outside.  The bun was greasy on the outside.  The veggies are not crisp or flavorful.  It's just not a good burger. Maybe I caught them on a bad day, maybe the 18th st location is great.  But I'm not going to waste my money trying to figure that out.  I do not feel lucky right now, I feel sad 😞

username: m i c h a e l

caption: Great team, awesome food!
Hot tiger bun is my favorite! Great lil spot with awesome prices.

Went to DC in February (Before Pandemic) from Toronto, and i still think about how amazing the burger was (Bogan Bun). Hopefully this franchises over the border. BEST BURGER SPOT. Also, the staff was very friendly and enthusiastic. Will be back once the border opens up again
Fantastic restaurant! On point with their Covid-19 protocol. Felt clean.  Had a Bogan Bun and a Mumbo Bun. Out of this world! The malt vinegar mayo is amazing!
Hair inside the bun and poor service .. never going there again
My first restaurant in dc and they didn't disappoint.

Great burgers, flat-pressed like you'd get from Shake Shack but richer with a more deeply savory taste. $$ for a wholesome double that has a smoothly-blended taste like what you'd get from a melt sandwich. Also - great staff that remember you months after a pre-pandemic grab n go. My favorite place for food at Union Market
I am definitely going their again. This menu does not disappoint. They have many creative flavors and their food is very high quality.

Staff was very friendly, owner was very rude and gruff with me for no reason, I asked a staff member permission to charge  my electric rideable inside and they said sure, then about 20 minutes later the owner comes by and very rudel says " I can't have you in here, you have to get out" no attempt at reasonable conversation, very poorly handled I won't go back, you shouldn't waste your time, tho I will reiterate all the staff I interacted with were prompt and polite

I’ve been waiting for some time to try Lucky Buns. I had visited their Adams Morgan branch several times to find it closed, despite it saying OPEN on Google Maps. When I finally got a hold on their burger, I was completely disappointed. Not worth the hype. To start, their patty is not juicy at all. The bread has no fluff to it, and finally the Lucky Buns sauce has nothing special about it. There are much better burgers in town. I won’t post their names here though.
Coming in, was skeptical. Left exceeding expectations. Grand burger. Knows what they’re with the black pepper in the burger. Picked this over chipotle. That’s how strongly I feel about this place.

Ordered through uber eats. Food was in the delivery car over 40 minutes. When it arrived the burger was a ball of cold ground meat covered by wet bread falling apart. The fries were cold, soggy and tasted like old oil. I called the restaurant and they told me to talk to uber because what happens after the food is picked up is not their problem. I ended up paying 35 bucks for a terrible meal and they could not care less.
Burger's one of best in my Lifetime. Not telling my age.  But have eaten s lot burgers 🤣😅😂

I don’t know anywhere else where I’d actually rather have a salad rather than a bun with my burger (you can choose between bun and salad here so no worries for traditionalists!). But Lucky Buns salad burgers (recent favorite is the Keu bun, with Gouda, pickled daikon, garlic mayo, sriracha, and other good stuff) and fried chicken (the Mumbo bun or Dirty Bird are 🔥 - you can get grilled chicken but the no-bun cancels the fried part, right?) come with a perfectly crunchy, green goddess-dressed salad that I would actually look forward to eating on its own. They also have BeerLao, occasional Thai pop-ups, and great cocktails (last one I had with bourbon, passion fruit, and sesame chili oil was uniquely delicious). If you sit at the bar you can watch Bob Ross/The Joy of Painting on repeat. The patio is great for summer. Staff is super friendly (and working extra hard right now to keep take-out going!).
Awesome staff and great drinks!

Waitress really not on top of things. Burgers for my girlfriend and I were way undercooked as well as being charged for double patties when we asked to why we couldn't get single patty burgers and no mention of double the price for double meat. 2 burgers patatas 2 beers $88.0 even though we were served raw meat no apology nothing. I can honestly saw I will never return and will tell anyone who will listen.Not worth the headaches

I am definitely going their again. Food was amazing. They have really great burgers, that are melty, fall apart in your mouth goodness. But if you ask me I would highly recommend the spice bag, which which is fried chicken, french fries, with a multitude of peppery spices, tossed in a paper bag( hence the name).A few helpful hints are, you have to get their before any meal time, or else it is hard to get in, and if you have a large party make a reservation.Also don’t sit out side during the summer time, you will get eaten alive by mosquitoes. Go and give this place a try, you will not regret it!!👍🏻😁
Chicken Cheesteak. An affront to most Philly purists, but just what the doctor ordered.

I love that this place is open late and it has really good vibes. Unfortunately the burgers and sandwiches are ridiculously overpriced, considering their “divey” atmosphere - $16 for a burger? Come on!
I had the chicky bun. I loved the idea of it and yet was a little underwhelmed. Maybe the chicken was a little too burned? It's still worth a go if you're nearby.
Oh my god. These burgers, Francine. These burgers. Oh my god, Francine, these burgers, oh my god.
When I'm craving a burger this is my go-to. The veggie burger is also really flavorful, as is the chicken. Always order a side of their mumbo sauce to go with the fries!

Lucky Bun is a burger place.  You will find most of the burger offerings to be double meat with Gouda cheese and often with a sauce.  The sauce is generously applied so these burgers are a mess to eat.  The sesame seed bun was good as was the overall taste of the burger.  Many people wash it down with drinks or cocktails which flow freely there.  There is also some grea outside table dining on a nice day.  The bartender was quite curt, which was not welcoming but otherwise the service was simply ok.
Great burgers and great staff.

I have never been disappointed by anything from here. Katsu bun? AMAZING. Bahn mi bun on salad? Heck yeah! OG burger? Alllrighttt. French fries also delicious, just wish they came with the burger. The decor inside is appropriately dive-y, the one issue is that it is smol. Go to the bar for takeout.
Good food for small location. Great burgers and chicken sandwiches.

Amazing staff! There was a long wait and it was a very cold night but we still wanted to try this place, so we sat outside and they gave us blankets and hot tea and made sure we were doing ok all the time! Super friendly, funny and just overall good people. The food was very tasty too! Thanks Lucky Buns :)
The food was outstanding. We sat outside at night under the heat lamps and they provided throw blankets as well. We got drinks, burgers, chick sandwiches and mumbo nugs. So good and cool atmosphere
Best Burger in all of DC, Western hemisphere, and the Southern part of the milky way

I ordered the Tiger Bun and it was not as spicy as it could have been. The Sichuan peppers were spread unevenly so I got a mouthful in one bite but that's it. My sister ordered the Spicy Bag, which literally just came in a bag with no plate (provided on request though). Service is fast and friendly but we waited close to an hour for a table, which, given the surfeit of options in the area, is probably not justified for subsequent visits.
Good cocktails and tasty/creative burgers.
Its great food. Burger was cook to perfect. I wish it was bigger lol

There are many disappointing boutique burger places in DC.  Lucky burger isn't one of them.  I've tried 4 different burgers and each of them beat more expensive burgers.  Lucky doesn't even serve them on brioche buns.  They don't need to!!!  The burger is that good.
Cocktail was good. Services as great.
Perfect place for  burger & drinks

OMG I am still thinking about the burger I had there the Bogan Bun...seriously a game changer! The bacon jam teamed with the other ingredients hit it out of the park. The beef was amazing. I was also really impressed with the team there. A beer we ordered was not available and they took the time to ask questions about our preferences for beer, the one they picked was awesome! I will certainly return and suggest that even if you don't live close you make the trip like we did.
Great burgers with great friends. This place is special, you can taste the heart and quality in this place.
Great burger. Horrrrrible service. The bartenders were so arrogant and rude. The burger is also over priced.
The bogan bun with the bacon XO jam Is simply amazing!!!!

I really wanted to give this one more star because in all fairness the burger was decent. I shared the bogan burger and the bhanmi chicken sandwich. Both sandwiches were adequate although the chicken was a little dry. My complaint comes from the 15 dollar price tag for just the burger. You can tack on another 7 dollars for a side of tater tots with curry sauce. Seriously, a 22 dollar plate for a burger should be outstanding! Maybe my expectations were too high because they certainly weren't met.
Great burger in a really energetic atmosphere.  Service was top class as well. Only bad point...my burger finished. Will be back in the next day or 2
Best Halal burgers in dc.
The food came out relatively fast for a sitdown restaurant. And it was good food. I think the Curry Chips might be my favorite
Legit .....best burger I've ever had in my life!!!!!!!!
An absolute gem. Fantastic food, superb cocktails.

Ah man the burgers here are great (as are the fries and salads). Really glad I tried this place. Definitely worth stopping in. The location is small and cozy. They are not great about answering the phone so.....
Great burgers!
Delicious burger
Grabbed a seat at the bar and had a great night. Bartender was able to help us pick the perfect cocktails. Burgers were a knockout.
They taste even better than they look.
Best burger I've ever eaten. And I once ate 15 burgers in the course of a week at an Atlanta burger competition haha. Great atmosphere too, and great servers.
Not that great ok for  late night
Just mouth watering...

Seriously the best burger I've had in a long time.  Very reasonably priced, too.  Staff was really friendly and on top of their game even though the place was packed.  This will be my go-to spot whenever I am in DC!
Sandwich was delicious at great prices. Staff were nice.

I purchased the chicken and beef burger and it was 17$ and it was a super disappointment!!! The sandwich was dripping grease, and the chicken was "burnt crunchy"..it was my 1st experience and I would NEVER return back to this place..maybe i purchased the wrong sandwich but 1st experience was everything and this was a no for me
This was quite possibly the best burger I have had in DC. The wait was about 15-20 minutes, but it was well worth it. Eat the Bogan burger and the tater tots.
Solid atomopshere and great Chicken Sandwich. Cocktails were unexpected.
May be known for burgers, but the chicken sandwiches are where it is at.
Great burgers! Staff was friendly and we got our food in 10 minutes! Highly recommend Lucky Buns!!

I would give it 5 stars if the beer was better. Wonderful food. I wasn't into fried chicken sandwiches until I started going here, and I only did because a friend was working there. Changed my life. To the managers: You still don't appear on google maps without searching, I guess they still want their pound of flesh.
One of the best burgers in D.C. Definitely going back again.

Got three sandwiches to go, the bun mi, the katsu, and the lucky burger. Everyone loved their sandwich. I had the bun mi with fried chicken thighs - tons of flavor and fresh cut cucumber and daikon. It had some fresh sliced jalapenos which were vibrant green and incredibly hot (beware if you dont like very spicy pepper). I also tried the katsu. It too was delicious but did not taste like a katsu curry, but more like a teriyaki sauce. Still very good though. Place was packed but all the staff was very nice.
Best burger ever
Amazing Burger!!!

(Translated by Google) This is where I ate my favorite homemade burger. The most regrettable eating American hamburgers elsewhere was that the burger buns were often bad. If you think so, please visit. It looks like you used a little softer bread. Even when cooking, you can enjoy a carefully cooked burger without burning too much bread. Burger Patty's baking is recommended for medium rare! Bar and restaurant with a mix of Hawaiian concepts. Brunch is available on weekends, but it's only 5pm on weekdays. Instead, it opens until dawn.  (Original) 최근에 방문했던 곳 중 가장 마음에 드는 수제버거를 먹었던 곳입니다. 다른 곳에서 미국식 햄버거 먹으며 가장 아쉬웠던 것이 버거 번 (빵)이 맛없는 경우가 많다는 것이었는데요. 그렇게 생각하셨던 분들 방문해보세요. 조금 더 부드러운 빵을 사용한 것 같습니다. 조리시에도 빵 부분을 너무 태우지 않고 성의 있게 요리한 버거를 드실 수 있습니다. 버거 패티의 굽기는 미디엄레어 추천합니다! 하와이언 컨셉이 섞인 Bar 겸 레스토랑 으로 주말은 브런치도 가능하지만 주중엔 오후 5시가 되어야 여니 방문시 참고하세요. 대신 새벽까지 문을 엽니다.
Loved it! Very spicy chicken!
The best burgers and chicken you'll find in DC.

The seating here is pretty limited, so be weary when going with a group, or you may have to wait an hour. They have indoor and outdoor seating available which is nice.  The burgers are pretty big, which is good. They taste great. The curry fries were good, but they aren't anything crazy. I would like to see more side options.  The server was friendly, I'd go here if I was already in DC, but I don't think I'd go drive there just to eat here.
Nice hangout with Al fresco dining options.  Very greasy fries.
Amazing burgers
ALWAYS GET THE DOUBLE!! Best burger I’ve EVER had!
Best burger in town
The veggie burger here is really good. Like you won't miss eating meat because the flavor and texture is great.

Good burger. A bit much on a smaller bun but then again that's kind of the point of a big burger right? I was totally satisfied and even felt a bit guilty... Guilty for pigging out and guilty for not finishing my fries. Lol

Great food, service, environment. Mumbo nugs and the Lucky Bun were especially good. Had some trouble getting the med rare burger to be actually med rare, but overall still a great experience. Highly recommend.

Definitely worth a visit if you like burger and fries. Got the three main ingredients of a good restaurant/bar - good food, good drinks, and nice staff. Favorite items on the menu are the lucky bun burger and the patatas bravas.
Burgers are top notch. And the bartenders are AMAZING
Get the hot tiger bun. Best sandwich ever.
The wait was WORTH it....Anything you get will be phenomenal. Trusttttt me, 10/10
Simply the best burger in Dc ... also like their fries with cury. Also like the fact that we can have the burger in a salad (without the bun).
When you're not quite sure whether you're craving a burger or a chicken sandwich more, you can solve your problem here.

10/10 Would recommend, but keep it how it comes! This place knows its stuff and to get the full experience you need it all. The single patty is good for a filling, lighter fare while a double will push to a full heavy meal, and don't forget the interesting choice of side options for the table. Truly a gem in the city and a place I will return. If not for the Keu Bun then for any of the other options.
Busy venue, cool decor and great location.  We sat outside at bar seating. We got our food within 10min of ordering and it was very tasty. Staff were really friendly.
Bun Mi burger is legit. Fast and nice staff. Will be back for sure.
Can be pricy for a burger, but the food never dissapoints. Highly recommend trying the chicken as well.

Such an awesome place to have a burger. They take burgers to the next level and beyond. It does get crowded so make sure you get there before you're really hungry or not you're going to be drooling waiting for a table.

I've been here twice and zero regrets.  Great food and staff.  It is small inside so make sure to go at a off peak time as there is no waiting area. Burgers are flat out amazing.  Definitely a place to take people if they are visiting or if you're a local and want quality.
One of us got a burger, the other the tiger bun. Both very good. We both thought the tiger chicken wasn't spicy but both were very very good and great flavors.

Impeccable service—best I’ve had in DC. The host greeted us and told us numerous times how much he appreciated us coming. We were quickly seated at the bar and enjoyed excellent drinks and fries. They lost our hamburger order, but the manager came and apologized several times and put a drink on the house. Will definitely be returning for delicious food and even better service.
Tasty and quick service :)

I split the patatas bravas with my friend. It was delicious. It had romesco (red bell pepper sauce) and garlic aioli as sauces. And they added some heavenly cheese curds to it. So good!  Then I got the crunch burger (veggie option) on greens. That lucky sauce is CRACK. Great texture 😍. Very filling!

This place is awesome! The menu/cocktails are extremely unique! I went one night while in DC for a work trip and had to go back before leaving because I needed to try more items from the menu. Amazing combination of flavors in the burgers. The bartending is seemingly taken as a craft where they literally craft your cocktails not just pour some ingredients and shake. Do yourself a "flavor" and visit this place just once. I guarantee you'll want more.
Spectacular.
Great burgers! Super messy though so be prepared to use lots of napkins and don’t wear white pants. Also $2 charge for tomato is kind of a lot but was delicious

Fantastic burgers and the one tots side was delicious as well. Will definitely be going back. It is a smaller place, but with some outdoor seating, it's not bad. If there is bad weather, it might be packed inside.
Delicious burger!! Solid cocktails too
No food because there was no chef??? We travelled a long way in the rain just to eat here. Very disappointed.

Great service, VERY fast even though the place was full. I got the spicy fried chicken sandwich and chips. If I were hungry I'd get a double on the chicken next time. Really crispy and we'll cooked, but thinner than a fast food restaurant meat portion. Muuuuch better and crispier than thicker portions of chicken though.  I'll definitely go back for more food, and I'd go for their drinks and beer selection alone.
Food is great!
Burgers were great and so was the ambiance!
Saw this on DDD and it was awesome. Service was so-so but food was amazing!
Some of the best. Burgers. Ever. Love their special sauces and the fries perfectly seasoned. Will come back
Might be the best burger in DC. Only uses Gouda cheese!!
Perfect spot to catch up with friends as it's not loud and has an outdoor space. The bartenders are often drunk which I find hilarious but can be offputting.

This is a great place to try some unique burgers! Ordered an appetizer and 2 burgers, and they were incredible! Food was quick, super tasty, and very affordable! The portions were perfect, a single burger fills up the small to average appetite and the double patty is great for those who are really feeling the hunger. The seating is limited, so be prepaired for a short wait on busy days, and it can get loud inside so I recommend the porch for those who dislike small crowded areas. I look forward to coming again!

Food at Lucky Buns is actually decent.  Unfortunately the owners are not.  Taste of Adams Morgan is a community event that happened last night where plenty of businesses partake in preparing some small bites and drinks for those who purchase tickets.  Lucky Buns decided that on the day of they were no longer going to participate while failing to inform event goers.  In lieu of supporting a local charity they hosted a happy hour for a big tech company.  As an Adams Morgan resident I won't be supportive of a business that isn't supportive of it's own community especially when it comes to charity.  If you're looking for burgers just go to Dukes or Bar Charley.
Great burgers, great beers, great service

Burgers are excellent but the service is poor;  starting with the hostess and moving to the bartender who is plain rude and gets overwhelmed for no particular reason. He  should not bartends if he can't handle a little pressure.
Best burger in DC!

Stumbled upon this place while searching for a late night bite to eat. I was wary of only seeing one vegetarian option on the menu but was pleasantly surprised to discover the burger was delicious, the drinks were expertly poured and the atmosphere was casual but not too dive-y. I highly recommend this place to a foodie!
Awesome place! Unique burhers and chicken thigh sandwiches. Great curry fries or vinegar mayo for proper fries. Love that they serve Mexican Coca-Cola!
Seriously juicy burgers... delicious!
Best Burger I have ever eaten.
Good bar!
Great restaurant!

We went to Lucky Buns twice and left as the wait time exceeded an hour and 30 mins. They take reservations for groups of six or more so I had to gather some friends but was finally able to try it and I have been back atleast three times since.  Amongst the group we had a variety of different sandwiches including El Jefe, Dirty bird, Chicky bun, Hot tiger, and the OG. We also shared orders of Patatas bravas and spice bag.  The El Jefe burger certainly lived up to my crazy expectations. It is a burger accentuated with a hatch chilli and gouda cheese. It was a subtly spicy burger that really hit the spot.  Two of the burgers warn you in advance that they are not subtle when it comes to spice. The dirty bird is on the milder side of the two and makes for a fantastic crispy chicken sandwich. The hot tiger is made with a chilli paste and the spice lingers for quite some time, both both sandwiches were well received and prepared very well.  As far as the burgers are concerned that leaves the OG and Chicky Bun both of which are essentially the plain options. They are that is name alone and both pack good taste and are prepared fantastically.  As for the sides the patatas bravas (smothered tater tots) were prepared crispy with a soft inside. The sauce that covered them was an enhanced version of a spicy mayo. Additionally, the spice bag which was fries (& Chicken) in a bag shaken with a spice mix and keeping with the theme they were prepared crispy and the chicken was very tender.  Overall, I would highly recommend this resturant. Lucky buns boasts great food and friendly service.

AMAZING! Loved this place so much — the vibe (before I knew it was meant to resemble a British pub I literally said to my brother “this reminds me of a British pub”). We all really enjoyed our meal — the chicken sandwich I got was amazing and everyone enjoyed their meal.
Super baller! Amazing veg burger. Make sure to get the curry fries!
Good. Not super but good
Amazing burgers! Get the Bun Mi with fried chicken!
Delicious burgers. I bet the chicken is good too, but haven't tried because of burgers.
My favorite burger spot in DC for real. If you want a perfect burger exprience, try a single patty. If you are hungry af, then go for a double patty.
Best burger in DC!
Great food, great service and great atmosphere. Recommend it to anyone who likes burgers and cocktails!
Their burgers are so scrumptious!
Best burger I’ve had in a LONG time. Up there with any of them. Minetta and all.
Really tasty burgers - went right before lunch closing so line wasn’t bad. Fries and burger were very tasty, one of the best in the city. Fast and quality service. Bet it’s packed at night
Good burgers and quick service.  Friendly staff. And economical for downtown DC
This menu does not disappoint! Great burgers (6oz) served single or double and delivered unexpectedly quick.  Tots were fantastic as well as the drink selection!
Burgers and fries are tops. Bartenders are badass.
Not a lot of options on the menu. Potato bravas are actually just tater tots.
The burger was fantastic and the food came almost instantly. Very small and busy place but still it did not take long to get a table.

Good food, good atmosphere, good vibes! It got really loud with the music at 6:15, which is the only reason I gave 4 instead of 5 stars. I work with the hearing impaired, so protecting hearing is very important to me. Besides that, I'll go back before the music is turned up next time!
Delicious food in a cozy and invitingly warm venue. Go for the garlic mayo and tots!
Best burger joint that's more than a burger joint in the city. Their cocktails rival michelin starred restaurants' cocktail programs as well, so don't be afraid to let the bartenders get creative.
This was the best burger I have had in DC.

Service was very friendly, food was delicious, and a nice atmosphere. Will definitely be back.  We went on a Sunday evening, and arrive shortly before opening, so we sat on the patio and waited for the restaurant to open. When it did we had our choice of tables (pick the front window, you get the most room), and staff came over quickly. Food is made to order, so there's a tiny wait, but it's so worth it, and it's not a long wait by any means. Both my fiance and I loved our burgers, I got the El jefe (the green chile was just the right touch of spicy) and he got the Beastie. Fries were yummy too! Overall, definitely worth getting there a bit early and waiting as the restaurant was completely full before our burgers were out. It's a small place when they don't have the patio open (we went at the end of February on a beautiful day, so waiting outside was pleasant but you wouldn't want to sit outside for a whole meal), but so so so worth it. We will definitely be back.
I ordered the Lucky Burger and my girlfriend ordered the El Jefe Burger. It was amazing!!
My favorite place for a burger. I always order El Hefe.

Just finished an excellent meal here. Started with drinks, I ordered off their cocktail menu, drink was wonderful! Started with their Patatas Bravas dont remember the name. I would come back for those alone. Burgers were juicy and unique. Cons (yes even for a 5 stars); wait was a little long, only because there was miscommunication and our table was given to someone else. I am not mad or upset in the least. We sat at the bar and waited, only wished it was communicated to us. Small, busy place, even on a Sunday evening, be prepared to wait. However, well worth it. We will be back!!
The food is so good... My favorite is the tiger bun
Great burger + curry fries! Great service! Busy spot!
Great Service, delicious food, but Soooooo expensive!!  $26 for a burger, fries, and soda!!

Had the Jeff burger and was greeted with a perfectly grilled medium rare pattie topped with a spicy aioli and fresh condiments. Great atmosphere makes for a fun weekend meal with friends or a date. Also, location just south of the main strip on 18th.
Veggie burger was a life-changing experience.
Great burgers and cocktails!

I had the bun mi burger and it was pretty good. I liked that it had a little bit of kick to it. My boyfriend got the lucky burger and he said it was the best burger he's ever had. I really liked their pickles, too. The thicker cut allows them to taste so much fresher and cucumber-y!
Really slow bar
After learning they take money from Andrew wheeler I won’t be returning and I’m retracting  my previous review.
Best burger in d.c.

We visited in the summer and sat on the patio which was nice. We ordered two burgers, which were really good quality and cooked quickly. The El Jefe was really good and spicy. I did not like the Bodan or the flavor of the bacon jam. The fries were good. The single patty was plenty of food for my husband and also for me.  The reason for the lower stars is because of another experience we had. We called to place a to go order and we were told to come in to place the order as they do not take orders over the phone. After walking 15 minutes there, the host said we were told wrong and that they only do to go orders when they are “not busy.” He offered us a table, but we left. We probably won’t return.
Fun vibe
Great sandwiches for an affordable price
The food is always good, the service - impeccable! Our food came so fast we looked puzzled!!😆
Best Burger I had that day!  #walkin #ADMO #liveworkeat #i❤️202 #niceVibe #seeyouagain
Excellent spot for Asian-american fusion burgers and brews

Enjoyed the burgers here at Lucky Buns. Got the Lucky Bun burger and was not disappointed. The flavors meshed well. The menu is simple, but it works. Would come here again, but next time would order the meat cooked through instead of medium rare because it was just a bit too raw/chewy ordering it the chef's preference that way.
Lucky Bun, Dirty Bird Bun and Proper Chips all superb. Super helpful and friendly staff. Also a great bar. So good food.
Fabulous drink, fabulous food
Their curry bag is die for !!!!
Excellent burgers -- maybe even the best in DC. Definitely get the handcut fries/chips. Yummmm!

I've had a lot of good burgers in my life and I was skeptical of this place, but it shut me up good. I split two burgers with a friend and every bite was heaven. Highly recommend trying a burger with some of the Asian flavors they play with.  My only very mild criticism was that their cocktail menu wasn't great. But it's burgers. Just get a beer.
Fantastic

I could seriously eat Lucky Buns all day everyday!! (Also secret tip, you can add friend chicken to your burger or a burger patty to your chicken sandwich but be warned, once you do it, there's no going back!!)  Sooo delicious!!
Amazing! I had a great burger and shared fries and really enjoyed my time there. The staff were super friendly and again, the burger was incredible!

The fact that their beef and chicken are halal makes this place a five star in my opinion. Pure and good meat is a must for a burger. We had the OG, Bun Mi, and Alfies. They were all amazing but my recommendation is to go with the medium well because the burger cooked all the way through is too well done. Otherwise, service and burgers are exquisite.
Awesome burgers and a great selection of beer. Staff was great. It was a pleasure dining here.
This is the second time in two months that I've come here and it was unexpectedly closed without any notice on Maps apps or anywhere else. It's also the last time I'll bother trying it.

Amazing burgers and all of their food is top notch, lot of thought and care put into each item. Cocktail program is second to none, some of the best bartenders in the city right here. Service staff kills is every time. Super friendly, anticipate what you need and have it for you.

Great spot for drinks and a casual meal. Basically serves burgers, chicken sandwiches, and one or two veggie options. However, don't let that deter you. They have many creative flavors and their food is very high quality. A cure for the boring burger! Highly recommend!
Only one word: Delicious!! Prices are good. In case you have to wait for a table, it's well worth it.
Delicious burgers!!

The only reason it wasn’t a one star was because the burger was actually pretty good although I would never call a rare burger medium rare and I had a surprise of what felt like a half of raw jalapeño in the middle of my burger when there wasn’t suppose to be any at all according to the recipe. The chicken wings are overpriced and mine were burnt but why complain for 4 wings that I paid around $15 for when you know you won’t be back. But also the server was not welcoming she just seemed very rude. The drinks here are straight shots of liquor I ordered a captain and coke and was told there was no rum then had to get a jack and coke and ended up getting a jack and ice since there was so much alcohol in my drink. I tried again with a Bombay and OJ and ended up getting a Bombay and ice so no luck the second time. But on the bright side if you want to get drunk real quick then go here I guess.
Small menu, very good food, good service, a bit crowded & loud inside. Has tough competition with some of the more established places that also do bar food - interested to see how they settle in.
Great service on every visit and the food rocks! Entire menu is delicious. Definitely my favorite burger place in the city. Psyched that they now do lunch!

Lets be clear. This place is a bar that happens to serve burgers. It doesn't serve food from 3-5pm and it closes the patio seating around 8, where you can order from a crowded bar (and wait for an hour) for a pretty good burger. If they were a restaurant, they wouldn't make it so difficult to get food, which is okay

1) 2 beers requested not available & waiter wasn’t aware. waiter offered completely different style of beers as substitute. Also waiter didn’t know what brioche buns were and asked how we wanted our chicken burger cooked....2) table of 2 beside us, ordered directly before us received their order 20mins before us. 3) order arrived & there were no chips (had ordered 2 portions, one with curry sauce). Requested & waited 5 minutes. Then the waiter checked which chips we ordered & promptly brought the wrong ones. We waited a further 5 mins until the correct ones arrived. 4) waiter asked if everything was ok. We said the burgers were cold & the waiter went ‘awesome’. I repeated they were cold & the waiter replied ‘oh’ and walked off. 5) finally, restrooms are dirty. Plus side they comped one portion of chips & a drink, & I’m sure burgers would have tasted great if they were hot.
Went for brunch today and I put this place as #1 burger in DC. So much flavor and I love that they use arugula which adds extra flavor. I can't wait to go back!

To sum up my experience - great food, absolutely terrible customer service. First of all, it does not say on google maps when you look up the place that the kitchen is closed between 3 - 5 PM on the weekends. So I got there at 4 PM and the hostess tells me the kitchen is closed until 5 PM so I ask if there is usually a wait at 5 PM and she says that there may be and it is different every day. I then ask if I can come back at 4:50 PM to get seated early and she says no. I then ask if I can wait outside until they are seating and she says that wouldn't be a good idea either. She literally was being as vague as one can possibly be about the best time to come back to avoid the wait when it was a simple question to begin with. Unfortunate that a place with such good food has such awful service.
Burgers here are great! Beers here are also good, but limited in draft selection. It's a small place and crowded because the burgers are good, so know what you're in for.

I visited Lucky Buns on Monday, September 3rd and got there at around 3:30. The food was really good and it was a decent vibe. However, there was one bartender that was obnoxious and likely drunk or hungover. He ended up getting an attitude with me when I asked him if he had a chance to grab the beer that I'd ask for 10 minutes earlier. I chalked it up to him having a bad day and ignored him but then noticed that he over charged my credit card. My gut tells me it was some sort of intentional payback on his part for displeasing somehow. It's really disappointing because the first bartender that was there when I arrived made me a great mezcal cocktail but he left when his shift ended and this other guy took over and made the whole experience unpleasant. Plain and simple - this one shady bartender is a cancer to an otherwise great hamburger spot.

I went to this establishment based on review and some word of mouth recommendations from colleagues. I was disappointed. I tried ordering one of the specialty burgers with the BaconXO jam to be told it was 86’d. Which I totally understand. So I ordered the basic Lucky Buns double with a side of the Curry Chips (fries). And had two of the $11 Japanese White Ale which you have to ask for a cold glass for. Really for $11!! It took quite awhile for the food to arrive and first came the Curry Chips before the burger. Why would the fries arrive in advance of the burger?  Timing seemed way off in the kitchen.  They were cold which seemed weird due to their open kitchen which seemed busy. I told the super polite and good Bartender and he apologiezed. He took them away and I watched as he consulultd with what must be a manager whom then proceeded to turn his back to me. He the manager never approached me to offer another dish or any apologies. The burger finally came and while good seems to have big chunks of far as well as two hard bites into what must hav been bone or cartilage (super gross!!).  I mentioned to the bartender when he brought the check it’s bad service a manager never approached me, he was apologetic but the manager seemed to be right there (the place is tiny!!) did not seemed to care about me. Poor service, cold food, and poor quality! Look elsewhere for a good burger is DC there’s lots of options! BTW- I’m a senior manager in the hotel business here in the city so I know poor service when I receive it!

I called to ask if all the food served was halal only to be greeted by a lady rudely saying “is ALL the food halal? That’s impossible... our meat is halal.” - safe to say I won’t be visiting to be helped by rude employees. First impressions are key and clearly they don’t care about getting new patrons.

Burgers are pretty good but the service is awful. Anytime I’ve been they don’t have enough staff working so it takes forever to get anything and the one server for the whole restaurant is overworked and forgets everything you asked for. Disappointing really. And the burger special sauce is not good.

I finally tried lucky buns today, and I declare my quest for the perfect burger in DC to be over. It should be called Perfect Buns, really! The burgers are amazing, for lack of a better superlative. They are definitely the juiciest burgers I've had in DC to date, and perfect mix of flavors. They also do unbelievable fries, cut thicker and fried super crispy with fluffy inside, which you can also get in the curry version (didn't try that yet). I love that on top of doing great food, the place has a very relaxed and super friendly vibe too. It almost looks too good to be true, but it actually is! Totally going back for another burger very soon!
Great burger- one of the best in the area. Staff was great and conversational. Ate outside and the mosquitoes were a pain but still a great atmosphere.
Friendly service and the burger was delicious.
Amazing, juicy burgers. Served with a smile. Recommended!
Burgers and chicken sandwiches with tasty twists, full bar and charming outdoor seating. Perfect place to catch up over a bite and near all the good spots in AdMo and Dupont .
Best burgers in DC and a killer staff.

Pretty good food and cute location! The service was a bit all over the place. There was a group of us trying to catch up and servers continually came to to check on us - which is fine, but it seemed like they just weren’t very coordinated.
Had a very good time here. The outside space is great, and the burgers too (I recommend the 'El Jefe' burger)!

I wanted to love this place, but after dining here, I wouldn’t write home about it. The atmosphere and people were cool and the music was great, but it was uncomfortably hot inside. We went during Sunday brunch and they were out of Bloody Mary mix which was odd. Also, you can only order your burger rare or well done which I didn’t like. For the price, you should be able to order your burger any way you like. My burger tasted ok, but it was insanely messy and I was unable to eat it with my hands. My burger also had a pineapple on it (yum!) but it still had the core in it which was very tough and impossible to eat. My friend got a chicken sandwich which tasted good, but it was extremely salty. Sadly, I don’t think I’d recommend this place to my friends, but I’d be willing to give it another try once they work out some of these details that were overlooked.
Emily and Kareem were amazing. Food was ABSOLUTELY AMAZING AND FRESH!  Great patio for chilling, and great environment for conversation. A must go!!!

The reason for the 2 Star rating is completely customer service based.  The first encounter with the hostess, proves she needs to be doing something other than customer service. We called in, to see about burger week, and she couldn't answer any questions, and kept giving rude answers. We arrived,and got to meet the hostess, and she was just as rude in person. I asked her what burgers are part of burger week and her response was " I couldn't tell you because I'm the hostess. You'll have to ask your server." Is it too much to know the most basic of questions, during the one week which is dedicated to burgers. YOUR HOSTESS SUCKS!!! PAY ATTENTION TO THE OTHER COMPLAINTS BELOW!!! We finally got seated outside, and was informed that all orders must go through the bar. So to recap, our experience, we were met with rudeness, we had to get up and go place our orders inside at the bar, and we had to get up to get refill our own drinks. So who do we tip??? No one!!! There was no service to deserve a tip. We then hear a waitress, actually take the order of the table behind us. Maybe race was a factor? Maybe it was because I had my kids? I dont know, but this needs to be worked on. The only reason I didn't give this one star, is because the only thing good about this place was that the burger was actually really good. The one that I had to go order inside, because I was the one  table that was too inconveniencing to have a waitress take our order. Will not return!  Update 1: I emailed you as requested!  Update 2: I emailed these guys, as requested, and there has been no response. They probably don't care.
Food was great but the hostess was really rude.

It’s finally a sunny day after a week of torrential downpours. I find out it’s DC burger week. It seemed like the perfect time to finally try Lucky Buns, which I’ve heard a lot about from food critics and friends.  While out before dinner, I tell a friend I’m going to Lucky Buns. She warned, “The food is worth it if you can get past the mean hostess.” I shrug off this comment finding it odd.  Our Uber arrives a few moments after seven. The restaurant is lined with empty tables. I point an empty table and say let’s sit at this one. By God out of nowhere a hostess stops me and says “We’re booked and you’re not getting a seat until 8:31 - no earlier.” It felt like a challenge. I told her to put my name down for four. She said “I said it will be over an hour and half. I will not call you until 8:31.” I accept the challenge. She pulls out scratch from under her podium that probably doubles down as weapon, writes my name down, and writes 8:31 and underlines it several times.  We go across the street to have a drink at another lovely AdMo establishment. My phone rings. It’s 8:24. I was pleasantly surprised. I answer and get a quick “Your table is ready” and click.  Over an hour and half wait, we picked up another to join us. We are directed to our table. The hostess stops and says “You said four. I wrote down four.” I ask if we can pull another chair up. “If you can find one and get it yourself, sure. But don’t bother anyone.”  The waiter comes up. He is knowledgeable. The meat is from a great farm in Kansas, the staff all come from fine dining, and they have lots of unique options. I order the lucky bun with bacon rashers and patatas bravas. I order one of their specialty manhattans. Everything was lovely and the food was delicious. One of the best burgers I’ve had.  At the end, my partner asks the waiter “What’s wrong with the hostess?” The waiter doesn’t show any sign of emotion or answer the question. It’s clear she is in control. And he is afraid of her. Maybe she is part of the experience. A right of entry.  We leave through the door without making eye contact with her. ‘Twas an experience. I’ll be back.  But if I’m not, you know who did it.  TLDR: food is great, staff knowledgeable, but you have to get past the hostess/bouncer first (look at other reviews to confirm). God speed and bon appetite.

Delicious burgers, cool vibes, one really mean hostess. Upon arrival, was told that we would not be seated before 8:31 (it was 7 pm and there were some open seats) for a party of 4 and questioned whether or not we wanted to return. When we got the call at 8:24, we were pleasantly surprised! Showed up with an extra friend and were told by the hostess there were no more chairs in the restaurant and that if we happened to find one, were warned not to disturb others. We found another chair and enjoyed our meal - the waiter was knowledgeable and provided delicious food and drink recommendations. Not sure why the hostess (based on reviews) is consistently unwelcoming.
HATCH GREEN CHILI in D.C. loved the El Jefe Burger and Happy Hour!!! Missing New Mexico? Go here!!!
Pretty good burger but the side salad at $7, was not that good. They left the dressing on the bottom of a small bowl. How are you supposed to toss it?
